Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a DRL-based framework for protocol design optimization.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on designing and evaluating networking protocols.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses DL-based solutions for protocol design.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes an AI-based approach for protocol design optimization.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with designing and optimizing a system (i.e., networking protocol).
